    "description": "<p><strong>Snowy</strong> consists of a fairly heavy flurry of snow, with the chill to accompany it. Ice-Types are quite content in the snow, and the cold has some knock-on effects that you may not expect!</p><p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Effects:</span></strong></p><ul><li>Ice-Type Attacks deal 30% more damage when they are Critical Hits.</li><li>Ice-Type creatures have their DEF stat increased by 50%.</li><li>At the end of the Round, non-Ice Type creatures lose a Tick of HP.</li><li>All Hazards gain the Ice-Type.</li><li>Ice-Type Moves and Physical-Category Steel-Type attacks have a 10% chance to inflict Frostbite 5. Attacks that would already cause Frostbite instead increase their chance to inflict Frostbite by 10%.</li></ul>"
  },
